                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment1787758_1887178&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2009-12-11 10:46:31Z, License: CC BY-SA 2.5&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Dec 11, 2009 at 10:46&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;So you&apos;re saying that because there are other ways to cause stack overflows, we might as well encourage more of them?&lt;/span&gt;

